/// # Transfer Services Package
///
/// This package provides SIP transfer capabilities through REST API and servlet implementations.
/// It enables blind transfers, attended transfers, and conference transfers for SIP communications
/// within the Vorpal Blade framework.
///
/// ## Key Components
///
/// - [TransferRestAPI] - RESTful web service interface for transfer operations with OpenAPI documentation
/// - [TransferServlet] - SIP servlet implementation providing B2BUA functionality with transfer capabilities
/// - [TransferSettingsSample] - Sample configuration class demonstrating transfer settings setup
///
/// ## Features
///
/// The package supports:
/// - Asynchronous transfer operations through REST endpoints
/// - SIP B2BUA (Back-to-Back User Agent) functionality
/// - Integration with the Vorpal Blade framework v2 transfer system
/// - Configurable transfer settings and analytics
/// - OpenAPI/Swagger documentation for REST endpoints
///
/// ## Architecture
///
/// The [TransferRestAPI] extends `TransferAPI` and implements `TransferListener` to provide
/// HTTP-based access to transfer functionality. The [TransferServlet] extends `B2buaServlet`
/// and handles SIP protocol operations for transfer scenarios. Configuration is managed
/// through the settings system with [TransferSettingsSample] providing example configurations.
///
/// @see org.vorpal.blade.framework.v2.transfer.api.TransferAPI
/// @see org.vorpal.blade.framework.v2.transfer.TransferListener
/// @see org.vorpal.blade.framework.v2.b2bua.B2buaServlet
package org.vorpal.blade.services.transfer;
